introduction.p:
The matrix A below is similar to a matrix of the form B below:
A \amp = \left[\begin{array}{rrrrr} 4 \amp 1 \amp 0 \amp 13 \amp 9 \\ -1 \amp 2 \amp 0 \amp -12 \amp -8 \\ 1 \amp 1 \amp 3 \amp 2 \amp 3 \\ 0 \amp 0 \amp 0 \amp 1 \amp -2 \\ 0 \amp 0 \amp 0 \amp 2 \amp 5 \end{array}\right] \text{,} \amp B \amp = \begin{bmatrix} 3 \amp \ast \amp \ast \amp \ast \amp \ast \\ 0 \amp 3 \amp \ast \amp \ast \amp \ast \\ 0 \amp 0 \amp 3 \amp \ast \amp \ast \\ 0 \amp 0 \amp 0 \amp 3 \amp \ast \\ 0 \amp 0 \amp 0 \amp 0 \amp 3 \end{bmatrix} \text{.}
(Treat the \ast entries in B as don't care values.)

